			<div class="post-242 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-events category-lokostyle category-recipes">
				<p class="postmetadataw">Posted by: <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?author=1" title="Posts by admin" rel="author">admin</a> | on October 18, 2012</p>
                <h2 class="post-title"><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?p=242">Now You See Them&#8230;Now You Don&#8217;t</a></h2>
				<div class="content-ver-sep"> </div>	
				<div class="entrytext">
  <p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/spooky-event-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-174" title="spooky event title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/spooky-event-title1.png" alt="" width="347" height="110" /></a></p>
<p>OK, so it’s true…ekoloko is <strong>HAUNTED</strong>!!! There are lots of strange things going on and weird stuff popping up all over the place!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/ghosts.jpg" ><img class="wp-image-243 alignnone" title="ghosts" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/ghosts.jpg" alt="" width="304" height="134" /></a></p>
<p>Some Ekos have even claimed to see…..GHOSTS!<br />
And the real question is: WHO are they really? WHO-WHO-WHO?</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style-title2.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-254" title="style title2" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style-title2.png" alt="" width="321" height="67" /></a></p>
<p>See what else our Ekos are wearing – as they search for the perfect look for Halloween!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style1.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-247" title="style1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style1.png" alt="" width="82" height="145" /></a><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style2.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-246" title="style2" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style2.png" alt="" width="95" height="134" /></a><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style3.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-245" title="style3" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style3.png" alt="" width="82" height="146" /></a><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style4.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-244" title="style4" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/style4.png" alt="" width="124" height="145" /></a></p>
<p>What are YOU wearing this year for Halloween? Tell us about your Halloween costumes for this year. We&#8217;d especially like to know if your costume is eko- inspired!</p>
<p>Write to <a href="mailto:usa_blog@ekoloko.com">usa_blog@ekoloko.com</a> and write Halloween in the subject of your message. And don’t forget to include your Eko name.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-109" title="Recipes title" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" alt="" width="274" height="89" /></a></p>
<p>Halloween is a good time for recipes with….what else? <strong>PUMPKIN</strong>!</p>
<p>Here is one that Chocolate Jim is considering for his café. Hope you try it out!</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Pumpkin Chocolate Chip Muffins</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Ingredients</strong><em> (Original recipe makes</em><em> </em><em>12 small muffins)</em></p>
<ul>
<li>3/4 cup white sugar</li>
<li>1/4 cup vegetable oil</li>
<li>2 eggs</li>
<li>3/4 cup canned pumpkin*</li>
<li>1/4 cup water</li>
<li>1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
<li>3/4 teaspoon baking powder</li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon baking soda</li>
<li>1/4 teaspoon ground cloves</li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon</li>
<li>1/4 teaspoon salt</li>
<li>1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg</li>
<li>1/2 cup semisweet chocolate chips</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="color: #ff9900;">*NOTE:</span> A 16 oz. can of pumpkin = approximately 2 cups of mashed cooked pumpkin.</p>
<p>If your cooked pumpkin pulp is too watery you can drain it in cheesecloth or a sieve. Or  you can keep cooking it to a thicker consistency in a sauce pan.</p>
<p><strong>Directions</strong><em></em></p>
<ol>
<li>Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Grease and flour muffin pan or use paper liners.</li>
<li>Mix sugar, oil, eggs. Add pumpkin and water. In separate bowl mix together the baking flour, baking soda, baking powder, spices and salt.. Add wet mixture and stir in chocolate chips.</li>
<li>Fill muffin cups 2/3 full with batter. Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes.</li>
</ol>
<p>As long as we are talking about pumpkins….now would be the perfect time to also learn…..</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/how-to-carve-title.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-262" title="how to carve title" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/how-to-carve-title.png" alt="" width="277" height="35" /></a><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Halloween-pumpkin1.png" ><img class=" wp-image-264 alignright" title="Halloween pumpkin" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Halloween-pumpkin1.png" alt="" width="116" height="88" /></a></p>
<ol>
<li>Cut a hole in the pumpkin at top</li>
<li>Scoop out the insides (you can save the seeds and roast them with salt and make pumpkin pie with the rest – YUM!)</li>
<li>Transfer your design – print the design on a piece of paper and use pins to trace it onto the pumpkin</li>
<li>Carve the features – remove the paper and carve along the dotted lines</li>
<li>Light with a candle in a jar or using holiday lights</li>
</ol>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/carve.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-263" title="carve" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/carve.png" alt="" width="509" height="131" /></a></p>
<p>Share your pumpkins with us!!! Send us photos of your creative carvings and we’ll be happy to post them on the blog! Only pumpkins please (no kids allowed in the pics). Send your pictures to <a href="mailto:usa_blog@ekoloko.com">usa_blog@ekoloko.com</a> – write “Pumpkin” in the subject and include your Eko name in your mail.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"> </div>
                <div class="up-bottom-border">
				<p class="postmetadata">Posted in <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=6" title="View all posts in Events" rel="category">Events</a>, <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=5" title="View all posts in LokoStyle" rel="category">LokoStyle</a>, <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=10" title="View all posts in Recipes" rel="category">Recipes</a> |   <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?p=242#comments" title="Comment on Now You See Them&#8230;Now You Don&#8217;t">8 Comments &#187;</a> </p>
				</div>
            
		                
                </div><!--close post class-->
	
				
			<div class="post-158 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-events category-lokostyle category-recipes">
				<p class="postmetadataw">Posted by: <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?author=1" title="Posts by admin" rel="author">admin</a> | on October 12, 2012</p>
                <h2 class="post-title"><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?p=158">Chef King</a></h2>
				<div class="content-ver-sep"> </div>	
				<div class="entrytext">
  <p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/events-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-22" title="events title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/events-title1.png" alt="" width="222" height="81" /></a></p>
<p>This weekend we are celebrating our love of food!!!!</p>
<p>We are talking about food, we are farming for food, we are sharing recipes, we are creating restaurants in our moon houses, we are playing food word games and MORE!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef-king-festival.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-159" title="chef king festival" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef-king-festival.png" alt="" width="894" height="475" /></a></p>
<p>Got ideas for food games you’d like to play? Send them to the blog before Sunday and maybe our managers will choose your game! Just write ‘Game’ in the subject of your mail, and send your idea, together with your Eko name, to usa_blog@ekoloko.com!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/style-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-35" title="style title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/style-title1.png" alt="" width="334" height="112" /></a></p>
<p>Look at what fashions we&#8217;ve been cooking up for you! This weekend the style is ‘chef’ – and some of these outfits are smoking hot!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef2.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-162" title="chef2" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef2.png" alt="" width="120" height="199" /></a><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef3.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-161" title="chef3" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef3.png" alt="" width="120" height="215" /></a><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef4.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-160" title="chef4" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/chef4.png" alt="" width="122" height="227" /></a></p>
<p>Can&#8217;t wait to see what they&#8217;ll be wearing tomorrow!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-109" title="Recipes title" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" alt="" width="274" height="89" /></a></p>
<p>And of course, our blog would not be complete without another great recipe or two! Hope you’re testing these out at home! Perhaps we could create the first ekoloko Chocolate Bean Jim’s cookbook!!! If you like the idea, keep sending in your recipes!!!!!</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Orange and strawberry smoothie </strong><strong>by motimot</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Ingredients:</span></p>
<p>2  cups sliced strawberries.</p>
<p>2  cups low-fat yogurt</p>
<p>½  cup orange juice</p>
<p>½ cup white or brown sugar</p>
<p>½ cup cold water or 7 large ice cubes</p>
<p>1 cardamom pod</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Preparation:</span></p>
<p>Mix all ingredients in a blender. Pour into shake glasses and enjoy!</p>
<p>+-+-+-+-</p>
<p><span style="color: #ff6600;"><strong>Biscuit cake recipe</strong> <strong>by Cchen222</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Ingredients:<a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/picture-of-cake.png" ><img class=" wp-image-168 alignright" title="picture of cake" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/picture-of-cake.png" alt="" width="233" height="177" /></a></span></p>
<p>2 packages of sweet (whipping) cream</p>
<p>1 package of Instant vanilla pudding</p>
<p>2 cups of milk, one for whipping and one for dipping</p>
<p>2-3 packages of biscuits</p>
<p>Some marshmallows</p>
<p>And some chocolate syrup</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">How to make:</span></p>
<p>Mix all liquid ingredients in a bowl (pudding, 1 cup of the milk and the whipping cream) until reaching a uniform cream</p>
<p>Then dip the biscuits in rest of milk (gently! No more than three seconds!)</p>
<p>Then arrange the biscuits in a pan (just one line)</p>
<p>Pour a quarter of your cream on everything ..</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Repeat this action several times </span>until you have used up the biscuits and the cream.</p>
<p>After you do all this, you can decorate with marshmallows or chocolate syrup or even graham cracker crumbs!</p>
<p>When you are done, insert the cake in the refrigerator for a few hours.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"> </div>
                <div class="up-bottom-border">
				<p class="postmetadata">Posted in <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=6" title="View all posts in Events" rel="category">Events</a>, <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=5" title="View all posts in LokoStyle" rel="category">LokoStyle</a>, <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=10" title="View all posts in Recipes" rel="category">Recipes</a> |   <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?p=158#comments" title="Comment on Chef King">5 Comments &#187;</a> </p>
				</div>
            
		                
                </div><!--close post class-->
	
				
			<div class="post-130 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-ekonews category-lokostyle category-rangers category-recipes">
				<p class="postmetadataw">Posted by: <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?author=1" title="Posts by admin" rel="author">admin</a> | on October 11, 2012</p>
                <h2 class="post-title"><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?p=130">Rangers, Recipes and More</a></h2>
				<div class="content-ver-sep"> </div>	
				<div class="entrytext">
  <p>This post is all about our Ekos – our newest Rangers of the Week, Eko Recipes, and some new Eko looks! Get ready to read about what our EKOS are doing!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/rangers-of-the-week-header.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-14" title="rangers of the week header" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/rangers-of-the-week-header.png" alt="" width="625" height="62" /></a></p>
<p>As reported, this week we chose SIX new Ekos to be Rangers of the Week. Our Rangers are chosen for a variety of reasons – but mainly because they have shown their dedication and loyalty to the ekoloko community, and are friendly, kind and helpful – both to Ekos and Managers!</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">So here are our new Rangers of the Week: Kim1234, Butterfly, Amit5000,Supercity, Jasper and Gabk720!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/rangers-week-4.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-131" title="rangers week 4" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/rangers-week-4.png" alt="" width="518" height="168" /></a></p>
<p>Congratulations to you all! Continue to make us proud! Woohooooooo!</p>
<p><span style="color: #c71585;"><strong>NOTICE*NOTICE*NOTICE</strong>: </span>ADVANCED RANGER CEREMONY TODAY will be postponed and held together with the Advanced Rangers in <span style="color: #c71585;">next week&#8217;s</span> ceremony on Thursday, October 18th, at 3:30 pm EST.</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-109" title="Recipes title" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" alt="" width="274" height="89" /></a></p>
<p>Here are some of the recipes we’ve received so far! YUM-MEE!</p>
<p>Don’t forget to try them at home – and make sure to have a grownup around if you’re not allowed to use the stove or oven alone.</p>
<p>Remember that food is always about sharing!  So keep sending in your favorite recipes!</p>
<p>Just write the word “Recipe” in the Subject of your mail, include your EKO NAME and send to <a href="mailto:usa_blog@ekoloko.com">usa_blog@ekoloko.com</a>!</p>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong>Jim’s Chocoloco </strong><strong>by matan078</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Ingredients:</span></p>
<p>¼ package of chocolate<br />
2 spoons of honey<br />
2 cups of milk<br />
marshmallows</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Preparation:</span></p>
<p>Break the chocolate into small pieces and put in a cup<br />
Heat the milk and pour half a cup into the cup with the chocolate and the honey<br />
Still until you get a smooth mix<br />
Pour half of the mix into two mugs<br />
Divide the rest of the heated milk into the cups<br />
Place a marshmallow in each cup</p>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><strong>Chocolate Mango Mousse </strong><strong>by idoXD1121</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Ingredients:</span></p>
<p>1 large mango<br />
8 ounces (200 gr) of quality dark chocolate<br />
Juice of 1/2 a large lemon<br />
1/2 can of coconut cream</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Preparation:</span></p>
<p>1. Cut the chocolate into chunks and melt them in a pot on low heat.<br />
2. While the chocolate melts, add the coconut cream and stir.<br />
3. Grind half the mango in a blender with the lemon juice.  Keep the rest of the mango on the side for serving.<br />
4. Add the chocolate and coconut cream mixture to the blender and blend again on medium speed.<br />
5. Transfer to serving glasses, cover and chill until mousse becomes firm.<br />
6. Decorate with slices of remaining mango and serve with ice cream.</p>
<p><strong>Mmmmm sounds yummy. Must try that at home!</strong></p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/style-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-35" title="style title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/style-title1.png" alt="" width="334" height="112" /></a></p>
<p>And don&#8217;t forget to check out what they&#8217;re wearing this FALL on ekoloko!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/maxwell1.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-144" title="maxwell1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/maxwell1.png" alt="" width="117" height="228" /></a>     <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/peaches.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-145" title="peaches" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/peaches.png" alt="" width="91" height="179" /></a>     <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/matan078.png" ><img class="alignnone  wp-image-146" title="matan078" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/matan078.png" alt="" width="82" height="168" /></a></p>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"> </div>
                <div class="up-bottom-border">
				<p class="postmetadata">Posted in <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=3" title="View all posts in EkoNews" rel="category">EkoNews</a>, <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=5" title="View all posts in LokoStyle" rel="category">LokoStyle</a>, <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=7" title="View all posts in Rangers" rel="category">Rangers</a>, <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=10" title="View all posts in Recipes" rel="category">Recipes</a> |   <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?p=130#comments" title="Comment on Rangers, Recipes and More">14 Comments &#187;</a> </p>
				</div>
            
		                
                </div><!--close post class-->
	
				
			<div class="post-108 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-events category-recipes">
				<p class="postmetadataw">Posted by: <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?author=1" title="Posts by admin" rel="author">admin</a> | on October 9, 2012</p>
                <h2 class="post-title"><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?p=108">Chef King Festival</a></h2>
				<div class="content-ver-sep"> </div>	
				<div class="entrytext">
  <p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/events-title1.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-22" title="events title1" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/events-title1.png" alt="" width="222" height="81" /></a></p>
<p>Pierre Milkyway has challenged all our Ekos to a ‘Chef’ contest – and he will not be beaten. Join us this weekend (Friday, Oct 12 – Sunday Oct 14) for our <strong>King Chef</strong> event and help prove to Pierre that you can match his skills!</p>
<p><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" ><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-109" title="Recipes title" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Recipes-title.png" alt="" width="274" height="89" /></a></p>
<p>This weekend we are celebrating <strong>FOOD</strong> with our <strong>KING CHEF Event</strong>! And what’s the best way to celebrate food? With some HOT CHOCOLATE at Chocolate Bean Jim’s Café!</p>
<p>And Chocolate Bean Jim has decided to share his secret recipe with all you Ekos out there as a special treat for this event!</p>
<p>Send us any changes you made to Jim’s recipe, or share your OWN recipes and we will post them on the blog!</p>
<p>Just write the word “Recipe” in the Subject of your mail, include your EKO NAME and send to <a href="mailto:usa_blog@ekoloko.com">usa_blog@ekoloko.com</a>!</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #993300;">Chocoloco by Chocolate Bean Jim</span></strong></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/09_Chocolate_Bean_Jim.png" ><img class="alignright  wp-image-111" title="09_Chocolate_Bean_Jim" src="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/09_Chocolate_Bean_Jim.png" alt="" width="134" height="163" /></a><strong>Ingredients</strong>:</span></p>
<p>¼ package of chocolate</p>
<p>2 cups of milk</p>
<p>2 marshmallows</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Preparation</strong>:</span></p>
<p>Break the chocolate into small pieces and put in a cup</p>
<p>Warm the milk and pour half a cup into the cup with the chocolate</p>
<p>Stir until you get a smooth mix</p>
<p>Pour half of the mix into the two serving cups</p>
<p>Add warm milk into the cups</p>
<p>Place a marshmallow in each cup</p>
<p><span style="color: #993366;"><strong>Share the yum!</strong></span></p>
				</div>
				<div class="clear"> </div>
                <div class="up-bottom-border">
				<p class="postmetadata">Posted in <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=6" title="View all posts in Events" rel="category">Events</a>, <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?cat=10" title="View all posts in Recipes" rel="category">Recipes</a> |   <a href="http://blog.us.ekoloko.com/?p=108#comments" title="Comment on Chef King Festival">7 Comments &#187;</a> </p>
				</div>
            
		                
                </div><!--close post class-->
	
					
